InEquality#

class pythontrees.operations.InEquality(inequality: str, strings_to_numbers=True)[source]#

Bases: object

Runs an inequality operation from an inequality string.

Examples

Running an inequality:

>>> inequality = InEquality("x == 10")
>>> inequality(x=7)
False

>>> inequality = InEquality("x == -10")
>>> inequality(x=-10)
True

>>> inequality = InEquality("y != 9.01")
>>> inequality(y=9.01)
False
